Local constants should follow naming conventions for constants
Why is this an issue? Shared coding conventions allow teams to collaborate efficiently. This rule checks that all local, final, initialized, primitive variables, have names that match a provided regular expression. 
### Noncompliant
public void doSomething() {
  final int local = 42;
  ...
}
### Compliant
public void doSomething() {
  final int LOCAL = 42;
  ...
}
### Noncompliant
{{BUGGY}}
